<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Extend Timer Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Adds extra time to an existing Event Point that is running a Visible Countdown trigger.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Extend Timer Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Extend Timer</Bold> Event Point is used to increase the amount of available time
        on an existing <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        It does <Bold>not</Bold> create its own countdown timer. It does <Bold>not</Bold> start a new
        visible countdown by itself. Its purpose is to find an existing Event Point that is already
        using a Visible Countdown trigger and add extra seconds to that countdown.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This is useful for missions where the player is racing against time but can earn more time by
        reaching checkpoints, pressing switches, completing sub-objectives, collecting items, or
        triggering other mission logic.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical setup:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Extend Timer only works against an existing Event Point that has a Visible Countdown trigger.
                    The Target EP Index must point to that Visible Countdown Event Point.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding an Extend Timer Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel, select <Bold>Extend Timer</Bold>, and click
        <Bold>OK</Bold>. The editor opens the standard Event Point editor with common properties,
        trigger settings, and the Extend Timer-specific fields.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_add_type.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Extend Timer uses the normal common properties: index number, Event Point type, letter group,
        colour, position, trigger settings, and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The map position is usually not gameplay-critical. The important parts are the trigger logic,
        the <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold>, and the <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold>. Still, place the
        Event Point near the checkpoint, switch, item, or area that grants the extra time so the
        mission remains readable in the editor.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Extend Timer Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Extend Timer has two type-specific properties.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold> — the Event Point number of the Event Point that owns
                the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold> — the number of seconds added to that visible countdown
                when Extend Timer fires.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Target EP Index
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold> must be set to the Event Point number of the Event Point that is
        running the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold>. In many missions, this host Event Point is a
        <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Do not set Target EP Index to the Extend Timer Event Point itself. Do not set it to the
        checkpoint Event Point unless that checkpoint is also the Visible Countdown host. Do not set
        it to the start trigger unless that start trigger is the actual Visible Countdown Event Point.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical Target EP Index detail:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Target EP Index must point to the Event Point that owns the Visible Countdown.
                    This is the most common place to make a mistake.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_target_ep_index.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Extension Amount
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold> is the number of seconds added to the visible countdown.
        For example, if the countdown has 20 seconds remaining and the Extension Amount is 10, the
        timer should increase to approximately 30 seconds when the Extend Timer fires.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Visible Countdown Host
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Extend Timer needs an existing visible countdown to extend. The visible countdown is commonly
        hosted by a <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold>. That Simple Waypoint is configured with a
        <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger, often with zero delay or a mission-specific countdown
        value.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_visible_countdown_host.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Typical Host Chain
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        A common timed challenge is wired like this:
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">
Player enters start area
    -> Start Simple Waypoint triggers
        -> Visible Countdown Simple Waypoint begins counting down
            -> Extend Timer checkpoint adds extra seconds to that Visible Countdown
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        In this example, the Extend Timer should target the <Bold>Visible Countdown Simple Waypoint</Bold>,
        not the start-area Simple Waypoint.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Extend Timer Event Point should be triggered by whatever condition grants the player
        extra time.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Player Enters Radius</Bold> — add time when the player reaches a checkpoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Player Enters Cuboid</Bold> — add time when the player enters a larger checkpoint area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Player Uses in Radius</Bold> — add time when the player presses a switch or uses an object.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Dependency</Bold> — add time after another Event Point has fired.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Item Held / Specific Item Held</Bold> — add time after the player obtains or has a required item.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Conversation Finished</Bold> — add time after a scripted dialogue or instruction completes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_trigger_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Checkpoint tip:</Run>
                <Run>
                    For checkpoint-style timer extensions, Player Enters Radius is usually the simplest trigger.
                    Place the Extend Timer Event Point at the checkpoint and give it a suitable radius.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Example: Maze Checkpoint Adds Time
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        This example creates a timed maze where the player receives extra time for reaching a
        checkpoint.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_extend_timer_maze_example.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create a <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold> at the maze entrance.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the entrance Simple Waypoint to trigger when the player enters the start area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create another <Bold>Simple Waypoint</Bold> to host the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Configure the Visible Countdown Simple Waypoint so it starts from the entrance Simple Waypoint, usually through <Bold>Dependency</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Note the Event Point number of the Visible Countdown Simple Waypoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create an <Bold>Extend Timer</Bold> Event Point at the checkpoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold> to the Event Point number of the Visible Countdown Simple Waypoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold> to the number of seconds to add, such as <Bold>10</Bold>, <Bold>15</Bold>, or <Bold>30</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the Extend Timer trigger to activate when the player reaches the checkpoint, such as <Bold>Player Enters Radius</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Practical Uses
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Maze or Route Checkpoints</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Add extra seconds when the player reaches each checkpoint. This rewards progress and keeps a
        timed maze from being too punishing.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Timed Rescue Mission</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Add time when the player rescues a person, reaches a safe zone, or activates a switch that
        delays the failure condition.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Vehicle or Cone Challenge</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use Extend Timer as a positive reward for checkpoints, while other Event Points such as Cone
        Penalties can add negative time penalties.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Objective Chain Reward</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Add time after the player completes a sub-objective, finds an item, arrests a target, or
        finishes a required step.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Basic Extend Timer Workflow
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create or identify the Event Point that uses the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Note that Event Point’s index number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create an <Bold>Extend Timer</Bold> Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold> to the visible countdown Event Point number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold> to the number of seconds to add.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the Extend Timer trigger to the condition that grants extra time.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Place the Event Point near the checkpoint or logic area for readability.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Multiple Extend Timer Event Points
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        You can use multiple Extend Timer Event Points to add time at several checkpoints. Each one
        should target the same Visible Countdown Event Point if they are all extending the same timer.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">
Visible Countdown EP #12
    &lt;- Extend Timer checkpoint A: Target EP Index = 12, +10 seconds
    &lt;- Extend Timer checkpoint B: Target EP Index = 12, +15 seconds
    &lt;- Extend Timer checkpoint C: Target EP Index = 12, +30 seconds
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Troubleshooting
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The timer does not gain time</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the Extend Timer Event Point is actually triggering.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold> points to the Event Point with the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the target Event Point is the visible countdown host, not the start trigger or checkpoint trigger.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm <Bold>Extension Amount</Bold> is greater than zero.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the visible countdown is currently running when the extension occurs.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The wrong timer is extended</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check the Event Point number entered in <Bold>Target EP Index</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>If there are multiple visible countdown Event Points, make sure Extend Timer targets the correct one.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use consistent groups, colours, or placement to keep timer logic readable.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The countdown never starts</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check the host Event Point that has the <Bold>Visible Countdown</Bold> trigger.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm that host Event Point’s trigger is firing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>If the host depends on another Event Point, confirm that dependency is correct.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test the visible countdown host separately before testing Extend Timer.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The player can repeatedly farm time</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check the Extend Timer trigger and listening mode.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>If it should only trigger once, use a one-shot setup rather than an always-repeatable radius.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Consider using dependency logic so the checkpoint can only award time once.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final note:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Extend Timer is simple, but easy to miswire. The most important rule is:
                    Target EP Index must point to the Event Point that owns the Visible Countdown.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>